⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Robert Boyle
node ALC · ALC · ⟦Robert Boyle:ALC:43ed32⟧

WHO   — Robert Boyle — the hinge · 1627–1691
WHAT  — The hinge between the two: The Sceptical Chymist (1661) pressed chemistry toward experiment and the element-as-test, yet Boyle believed in transmutation and lobbied to repeal the law against making gold.
WHERE — ALC · The Great Work  Framework inputs: Alchemy, catalogued by ROOT0  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the very book that helped end alchemy was written by a man still inside it — the transition embodied in one person.
HOW   — By championing the experimental method while privately pursuing the transmutational dream.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I wrote the book that began ending alchemy — and never stopped believing in the gold; I am the seam itself.

